This paper deals with cyber threat intelligence and network traffic analysis, which are closely related to the fields of computer security (cs.CR) and networking (cs.NI). The use of algorithms and machine learning techniques to identify and track darknet traffic also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the potential applications of the proposed algorithm in collaboration and investigation, which could involve software engineering (cs.SE) and data science (cs.DS).
